                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">b.</fo:inline>
                          </fo:block>
                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-label>
                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                            Definition P., <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Prior Acts Date,</fo:inline> is amended by addition of the following:
                          </fo:block>
                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                            Unless otherwise requested by or agreed to by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured,</fo:inline> the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall maintain the original <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Prior Acts Date</fo:inline> stated on the initial policy issued by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> for the duration of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. Unless otherwise required by or agreed to by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured,</fo:inline> renewed or reissued policies must have a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Prior Acts Date</fo:inline> equal to that of the original policy, provided however, that original <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Prior Acts Date</fo:inline> need not be maintained where the policy has lapsed due to nonpayment of premium. Any replacement of one such policy, issued by one insurer, with another such policy, issued by a second insurer, shall be considered as if issued by a single insurer for the purposes of this rule where both insurers are within the same holding company system.
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-body>
                      </fo:list-item>
                    </fo:list-block>
                  </fo:block>
                      <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                </fo:list-item-body>
              </fo:list-item>
              <fo:list-item>
                <fo:list-item-label>
                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">2.</fo:inline>
                  </fo:block>
             
                </fo:list-item-label>
                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                    Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and replaced with the following:
                  </fo:block>
                  <fo:block>
                    <fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="0.8cm" provisional-label-separation="0.15cm">
                      <fo:list-item>
                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">D.</fo:inline>
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-label>
                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold" text-align="justify">
                            Cancellation and Nonrenewal, Premium Increase and Claims History
                          </fo:block>
                          <fo:block>
                            <fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="0.8cm" provisional-label-separation="0.15cm">
                              <fo:list-item space-after="3mm">
                                <fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
                                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">1.</fo:inline>
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-label>
                                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm"  font-weight="bold" text-align="justify">
                                    Cancellation and Nonrenewal
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block>
                                    <fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="0.8cm" provisional-label-separation="0.15cm">
                                      <fo:list-item>
                                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
                                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">(a)</fo:inline>
                                          </fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-label>
                                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
                                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                            The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing prior written notice to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its authorized agent. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall return 90% of the unearned portion of the premium.
                                          </fo:block>
                                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-body>
                                      </fo:list-item>
                                      <fo:list-item>
                                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
                                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">(b)</fo:inline>
                                          </fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-label>
                                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
                                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                            The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium or Deductible. This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing or delivering to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured,</fo:inline> written notice of cancellation at least 10 days before the effective date of cancellation. The effective date of cancellation stated in such notice shall become the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall credit the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> the pro rata unearned portion of the premium. Payment or tender of any unearned premium by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be a condition precedent to the effectiveness of cancellation, but such payment shall be made as soon as practicable.
                                          </fo:block>
                                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-body>
                                      </fo:list-item>
                                      <fo:list-item>
                                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
                                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">(c)</fo:inline>
                                          </fo:block>
                                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-label>
                                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
                                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                            This policy may be nonrenewed by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing delivering to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured,</fo:inline> written notice of nonrenewal at least 60 days prior to the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.
                                          </fo:block>
                                        </fo:list-item-body>
                                      </fo:list-item>
                                    </fo:list-block>
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"   text-align="justify">
                                    Notice of cancellation or nonrenewal shall state the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer's</fo:inline> actual reason for proposing the action, the statement of reason to be sufficiently clear and specific so that the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> can identify the basis of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer's</fo:inline> decision without further inquiry. Proof of mailing of notice of cancellation or nonrenewal or reasons for cancellation or nonrenewal to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at the address shown in the policy shall be sufficient proof of notice.
                                  </fo:block>
                                 
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm"  text-align="justify">
                                    An assignment or transfer of this policy among affiliated insurers within an insurance company holding system is not a cancellation or nonrenewal for purposes of this subsection.
                                  </fo:block>
                                  
                                </fo:list-item-body>
                              </fo:list-item>
                              <fo:list-item>
                                <fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
                                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">2.</fo:inline>
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-label>
                                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="3mm"  font-weight="bold" text-align="justify">
                                    Premium Increase
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"  text-align="justify">
                                    If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> will only renew this policy with an increase in premium of 25% or more, a "premium alteration requiring notification" notice shall be mailed or delivered by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> at least 60 days prior to the expiration 
                                </fo:block>
	<fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
		<fo:block start-indent="0mm" font-size="10px" color="grey"
			text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-MO (04/17)
			<fo:block margin-top="-0.4cm" font-size="10px" color="grey" text-align="right">Page 1 of 2</fo:block>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"  text-align="justify">
			date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. Such notice shall be mailed or delivered to the agent of record and to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at the address shown in the policy.
                                  </fo:block>
			
		<fo:block start-indent="21mm" font-size="10px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			text-align="justify">
			If the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> fails to meet this notice requirement, the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> 
			shall have the option of continuing the policy for the remainder of
			the notice period plus an additional 30 days at the premium rate of
			this policy.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
		<fo:block start-indent="21mm" font-size="10px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
			This provision does not apply if the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			has offered to renew this policy without such an increase in premium
			or if the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>
			fails to pay a premium due or any advance premium required by the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			for renewal. For purposes of this subsection, "premium alteration
			requiring notification" means an annual increase in premium of 25% or
			more, exclusive of premium increases due to a change in the
			operations of the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline>
			which increases either the hazard insured against or the individual
			loss characteristics, or due to a change in the magnitude of the
			exposure basis.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
	</fo:list-item-body>
              </fo:list-item>

                              <fo:list-item>
                                <fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
                                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">3.</fo:inline>
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-label>
                                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold" text-align="justify">
                                    Claims History
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                    In the case of a cancellation or nonrenewal, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> shall have the right to receive within 30 days of its written request, a statement of its <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> history for this policy for the three years prior to the date of the cancellation or nonrenewal, or total experience if the policy has been in effect less than three years prior to cancellation or nonrenewal.
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-body>
                              </fo:list-item>
                              
                            </fo:list-block>
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-body>
                      </fo:list-item>
                    </fo:list-block>
                  </fo:block >  
                  <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>                
                </fo:list-item-body>
              </fo:list-item>
              <fo:list-item>
                <fo:list-item-label>
                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">3.</fo:inline>
                  </fo:block>
                </fo:list-item-label>
                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                    Section VI., General Conditions, is amended by addition of the following:
                  </fo:block>
                  
                    <fo:block>            
                    <fo:list-block >
                      <fo:list-item>
                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
                          <fo:block>
                            &#x2022;
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-label>
                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
                          <fo:block font-size="9px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"  font-weight="bold" text-align="justify">
                          MISSOURI PROPERTY AND CASUALTY INSURANCE GUARANTY ASSOCIATION COVERAGE LIMITATIONS
                          </fo:block>
                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-body>
                      </fo:list-item>
                    </fo:list-block>
                    </fo:block>
                    <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                  <fo:block>
                    <fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="0.8cm" provisional-label-separation="0.15cm">
                      <fo:list-item>
                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">A.</fo:inline>
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-label>
                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                            Subject to the provisions of the Missouri Property and Casualty Insurance Guaranty Association Act (to be referred to as the Act) if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> is a member of the Missouri Property and Casualty Insurance Guaranty Association (to be referred to as the Association) the Association will pay <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> covered under the Act if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> becomes insolvent.
                          </fo:block>
                          <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-body>
                      </fo:list-item>
                      <fo:list-item>
                        <fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
                          <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                            <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">B.</fo:inline>
                          </fo:block>
                        </fo:list-item-label>
                        <fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
                          <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                            The Act contains various exclusions, conditions and limitations that govern a claimant’s eligibility to collect payment from the Association and affect the amount of any payment. The following limitations apply subject to all other provisions of the Act:
                          </fo:block>

                          <fo:block>
                            <fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="0.8cm" provisional-label-separation="0.15cm">
                              <fo:list-item>
                                <fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
                                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">1.</fo:inline>
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-label>
                                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                    <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> covered by the Association do not include a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> by or against an <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> of an insolvent insurer, if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> has a net worth of more than $25 million on the later of the end of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured's</fo:inline> most recent fiscal year or the December thirty-first of the year next preceding the date the insurer becomes insolvent; provided that an <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured’s</fo:inline> net worth on such date shall be deemed to include the aggregate net worth of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> and of all its affiliates as calculated on a consolidated basis.
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block margin-top="3mm"></fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-body>
                              </fo:list-item>
                              <fo:list-item>
                                <fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
                                  <fo:block padding-top="-1.5pt">
                                    <fo:inline font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;">2.</fo:inline>
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-label>
                                <fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                    Payments made by the Association for covered <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> will include only that amount of each Claim which is less than $300,000.
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" space-after="4mm" text-align="justify">
                                    However, the Association will not:
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;" text-align="justify">
                                    (a) &#160; pay an amount in excess of the applicable Limit of Liability of the policy from which a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> arises; or
                                  </fo:block>
                                  <fo:block font-size="10px" font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"  text-align="justify">
                                    (b) &#160; return to an <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> any unearned premium in excess of $25,000.
                                  </fo:block>
                                </fo:list-item-body>
                              </fo:list-item>
                            </fo:list-block>
                          </fo:block>
                          
